<subSubSection id="4ED78790F36E5E203F835BB940A6FD79" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0672D41BF36E5E203F835BB94163FE7A" blockId="19.[151,1435,1947,2008]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1437,151,644]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="34B90809F36E5E273F835BB94164F825" bold="true" box="[199,315,1984,2008]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
Currently, two subspecies are recognized within 
<taxonomicName id="C1CDAF98F36E5E273C285BB84477F825" box="[876,1064,1984,2008]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiotreta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="valenciennesi">
<emphasis id="34B90809F36E5E273C285BB843DFF825" box="[876,896,1985,2008]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<collectingCountry id="7EDA948BF36E5E273C285BB843DFF825" box="[876,896,1985,2008]" name="Iceland" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">O</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="34B90809F36E5E273CD45BB94477F825" box="[912,1064,1984,2008]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">valenciennesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the nominate Indo-Pacific form and the Atlanto-Mediterranean 
<taxonomicName id="C1CDAF98F3695E203EBD5CE1438FFF52" authority="Koehler, 1896" authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1896" box="[505,976,151,176]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiotreta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subSpecies" species="valenciennesi" subSpecies="rufescens">
<emphasis id="34B90809F3695E203EBD5CE14252FF52" box="[505,525,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<collectingCountry id="7EDA948BF3695E203EBD5CE14252FF52" box="[505,525,152,175]" name="Iceland" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">O</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="34B90809F3695E203D585CE14379FF4D" box="[540,806,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">valenciennesi rufescens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="625CA9EAF3695E203C695CEE438FFF52" author="Koehler" box="[813,976,151,175]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Koehler, R. (1896) Note preliminaire sur les Ophiures des premieres campagnes de la &quot; Princesse Alice. &quot; Memoirs Societe Zoologique de France, 9, 241 - 253." type="journal article" year="1896">
Koehler, 
<number id="B005C63CF3695E203CD15CEE438FFF52" box="[917,976,151,175]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1896.0">1896</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The differences between these are more rugose disk granules and longer adoral shields in the nominate subspecies (
<bibRefCitation id="625CA9EAF3695E203B465CC544F4FF29" author="Paterson" box="[1026,1195,188,212]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Paterson, G. L. J. (1985) The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Zoology Series, 49, 1 - 162." type="journal article" year="1985">
Paterson 
<number id="B005C63CF3695E203B2B5CC544F4FF29" box="[1135,1195,188,212]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="625CA9EAF3695E203B855CC445C3FF29" author="Mortensen" box="[1217,1436,188,212]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Mortensen, T. (1933 b) Ophiuroidea. The Danish Ingolf Expedition, 4, 1 - 121." type="journal article" year="1933" yearSuffix="b">
Mortensen (
<number id="B005C63CF3695E203A0F5CC545DAFF29" box="[1355,1413,188,212]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1933.0">1933</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
observed a large variability in the oral shields of Atlantic specimens, which he referred to 
<emphasis id="34B90809F3695E203BE25C99454FFF05" box="[1190,1296,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">rufescens</emphasis>
, because he found them different from typical 
<taxonomicName id="C1CDAF98F3695E203D515D7D42F2FEE1" box="[533,685,260,284]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiotreta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="valenciennesi">
<emphasis id="34B90809F3695E203D515D7D42F2FEE1" box="[533,685,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">valenciennesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This distinction cannot be maintained though, since Pacific specimens fall within the variability of 
<emphasis id="34B90809F3695E203D5C5D5142DDFEBD" box="[536,642,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">rufescens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="625CA9EAF3695E203DD55D5E43D9FEC2" author="O'Hara" box="[657,902,295,319]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="O'Hara, T. D. &amp; Stohr, S. (2006) Deep water Ophiuroidea (Echinodermata) of New Caledonia: Ophiacanthidae and Hemieuryalidae. Tropical Deep Sea Benthos (Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle 193), 24, 33 - 141." type="journal article" year="2006">
O'Hara &amp; Stöhr 
<number id="B005C63CF3695E203C0F5D5E43D9FEC2" box="[843,902,295,319]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, and Lifou material). Given the high variability of several characters it is possible that these forms represent a species complex, but a subspecies distinction cannot be maintained.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0672D41BF3695E203F835DED40A6FD79" blockId="20.[151,1437,151,644]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
The delimitation of 
<taxonomicName id="C1CDAF98F3695E203EE25DED427FFE51" box="[422,544,404,428]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiotreta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="34B90809F3695E203EE25DED427FFE51" box="[422,544,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ophiotreta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="C1CDAF98F3695E203D215DED42A7FE51" box="[613,760,404,428]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiacantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="34B90809F3695E203D215DED42A7FE51" box="[613,760,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ophiacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rests mainly on the usually spatulate shape of the distal oral papilla in 
<emphasis id="34B90809F3695E203E415DC14273FE2D" box="[261,556,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName id="C1CDAF98F3695E203E415DC14120FE2D" box="[261,383,440,464]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiotreta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Ophiotreta</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="625CA9EAF3695E203ECA5DC1427BFE2D" author="Verrill" box="[398,548,440,464]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Verrill, A. E. (1899 b) Report on the Ophiuroidea collected by the Bahama expedition in 1893. Bulletin from the Laboratories of Natural History of the State University of Iowa, 5, 1 - 86." type="journal article" year="1899" yearSuffix="b">
Verrill 
<number id="B005C63CF3695E203E995DC14249FE2D" box="[477,534,440,464]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1899.0">1899</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
. This character has however also been shown for 
<taxonomicName id="C1CDAF98F3695E203B125DC14174FE09" authority="Bruzelius, 1805" authorityName="Bruzelius" authorityYear="1805" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiacantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="bidentata">
<emphasis id="34B90809F3695E203B125DC14506FE2D" box="[1110,1369,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ophiacantha bidentata</emphasis>
(Bruzelius, 
<number id="B005C63CF3695E203FAC5DA5417CFE09" box="[232,291,476,500]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1805.0">1805</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="D9766AB9F3695E203E205DA441CBFE08" box="[356,404,477,501]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="C1CDAF98F3695E203D525DA54455FE09" authority="Martynov &amp; Litvinova 2008" authorityName="Martynov &amp; Litvinova" authorityYear="2008" box="[534,1034,476,500]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiacantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="34B90809F3695E203D525DA542F7FE09" box="[534,680,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ophiacantha</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="625CA9EAF3695E203DFD5DA5445CFE09" author="Martynov" box="[697,1027,476,500]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Martynov, A. V. &amp; Litvinova, N. M. (2008) Deep-water Ophiuroidea of the northern Atlantic with descriptions of three new species and taxonomic remarks on certain genera and species. Marine Biology Research, 4, 76 - 111." type="journal article" year="2008">
Martynov &amp; Litvinova 
<number id="B005C63CF3695E203C825DA5445CFE09" box="[966,1027,476,500]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Another generic character, the flat and serrated arm spines, is shared by 
<taxonomicName id="C1CDAF98F3695E203D065E794291FDE5" box="[578,718,512,536]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiopristis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="34B90809F3695E203D065E794291FDE5" box="[578,718,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ophiopristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of which 
<taxonomicName id="C1CDAF98F3695E203C0E5E79439BFDE5" box="[842,964,512,536]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiotreta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="34B90809F3695E203C0E5E79439BFDE5" box="[842,964,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ophiotreta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
originally was a subgenus (Verrill 
<number id="B005C63CF3695E203A105D8645D0FDEA" box="[1364,1423,511,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1899.0">1899</number>
), and by 
<taxonomicName id="C1CDAF98F3695E203FA85E5D4137FDC1" box="[236,360,548,572]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="34B90809F3695E203FA85E5D4137FDC1" box="[236,360,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ophiocopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggesting possible affinities between these genera, which were placed in three different subfamilies (
<bibRefCitation id="625CA9EAF3695E203FBB5E3E41FBFDA2" author="Paterson" box="[255,420,583,607]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Paterson, G. L. J. (1985) The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Zoology Series, 49, 1 - 162." type="journal article" year="1985">
Paterson 
<number id="B005C63CF3695E203E2C5E3E41FBFDA2" box="[360,420,583,607]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This may be additional evidence supporting Martynov's (
<number id="B005C63CF3695E203B765E3E4432FDA2" box="[1074,1133,583,607]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2010.0">2010</number>
b) decision to drop the subfamilies.
</paragraph>
